name: Sad powers
description:
You're given Q queries of the form (L, R). For each query you have to find the
number of such x that L ≤ x ≤ R and there exist integer numbers a > 0, p > 1
such that x = a^p. Input The first line contains the number of queries Q (1 ≤
Q ≤ 10^5). The next Q lines contains two integers L, R each (1 ≤ L ≤ R ≤
10^18). Output Output Q lines — the answers to the queries. Example Input 6 1
4 9 9 5 7 12 29 137 591 1 1000000 Output 2 1 0 3 17 1111 Note In query one the
suitable numbers are 1 and 4.
